Description:
No annotation on the envelope.

  • First subfolder (Annotation: "Rubens Selbsbildnis (H. Cramer)") addressed (inside) to "Institut f. Kunstgeschichte d. Techn. Hochschule 6100 Darmstadt Techn. Hochschule" and dated 08.05.1967:
    • Notes about Rubens' Self-portrait
    • Correspondence with H. M. Cramer (dated 1966-67) and Sabena newspaper advertising
    • Photos of Rubens' Self-portrait
    • Correspondence with H. F. van Zijst dated 1967
  • Second subfolder (Annotation: "Rubens Selbstbildnis Exemplar in Rom 1968") addressed (inside) "Herrn Professor Dr. phil. habil. Hans-Gerh. Evers 6101 Traisa Waldstr. 43" and dated 28.06.1968:
    • Photos of Rubens' Self-portrait
    • Notes about 'The Four Philosophers' (dated 1968) and the Self-portrait
    • Correspondence with Thomas L. Roser (dated 1968/1972), with Luisa Becherucci (dated 1968), with Ulrich Middeldorf (1968)
  • Photos of portraits of Rubens and his family
  • Photocopies of the correspondence with Louis Malbos (dated 1967)
  • Bibliographic references
  • Correspondence with Bruno Lohse (dated 1959), with Karla Langedijk (dated 1967), with G. Cramer (dated 1967)
  • Notes about Rubens' Self-portraits (dated 1967)
  • Draft text about Rubens' self-portraits
  • Third subfolder (Annotation: "Rubens Selbsbildnis") addressed (inside) to "Herrn Professor Dr. H. G. Evers Institut f√ºr Kunstgeschichte an der Technischen Hochschule 61 Darmstadt Hochschulstr. 1":
    • Extracts from different publications
    • Correspondence with F. Baudouin (dated 1967)
    • Notes about Rubens' Self-portrait (dated 1966)
    • Photocopies (from a catalogue) about Rubens' portraits
  • Photos of Rubens' pitcher, box and self-portrait and Helena Fourment's necklace
